#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:0
msgid "The end (of Windows 10) is nigh!"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:6
msgid ""
"*Today we're launching \"End Of 10\" ([endof10.org](https://endof10.org/)) "
"and bringing Linux to Windows 10 users!*"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:8
msgid ""
"On 14 October 2025, Microsoft will end support for Windows 10. Microsoft "
"will no longer provide updates for the system and this will turn an "
"estimated 200 to 400 million laptops and computers worldwide into security "
"risks and heavily polluting e-waste."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:10
msgid "Yours may be one of them."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:12
msgid "<!--more-->\n"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:14
msgid ""
"But what if you could make your current computer fast and secure again so "
"you can continue to use it? There is an alternative to Windows, one that is "
"free, receives regular updates and works on nearly all devices, from most "
"smartphones and routers, to supercomputers that predict the weather and "
"robots on Mars."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:16
msgid ""
"Yes, it's Linux. Linux is extremely flexible and adaptable, and it can work "
"for you too. Linux can run smoothly on your latest laptop and on a machine "
"from 10-20 years ago."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:18
msgid ""
"The cheapest and most environmentally-friendly computer is the one you "
"already own."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:20
msgid ""
"Installing a new operating system may sound difficult, but the community "
"behind the \"End Of 10\" is here to help! In towns and cities around the "
"globe, there are people and places ready to lend you a hand or even install "
"Linux for you. Many more helper groups get added every day."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:22
msgid "Find help near you at our website:"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:24
msgid "https://endof10.org/"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:26
msgid "Why can't I just migrate my current machine to Windows 11?"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:28
msgid ""
"Because there is a good chance it won't meet the system requirements for "
"Windows 11. There are several reasons for this, but one of the most "
"questionable is that many devices are being rejected for not having a modern"
" security module. From a technical standpoint, thatâ€™s hard to justify."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:30
msgid ""
"Ironically, it just so happens that 14 October is also \"[International "
"E-Waste Day](https://weee-forum.org/iewd-about/)\". Shortly after follows "
"\"[International Repair Day](https://openrepair.org/international-repair-"
"day/)\" on 18 October. You can't make these things up!"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:32
msgid ""
"But Microsoft really wants Windows 10 users to buy new hardware. In fact, "
"the company has [pushed full-screen "
"notifications](https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2024/11/microsoft-pushes-"
"full-screen-ads-for-copilot-pcs-on-windows-10-users/) onto users' screens "
"encouraging them to do just that â€” even for computers that are able to "
"upgrade to Windows 11. This means manufacturing and transporting hundreds of"
" millions of new devices, and this is perhaps the biggest waste of all. "
"Hardware production alone consumes copious amounts of energy and has a "
"disproportionate carbon footprint, all of which is for absolutely nothing "
"when a working device lands in the bin."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:34
msgid ""
"On the other hand, when you choose Linux, you get everything you could ever "
"want for daily use, and the same machine can be working for decades. Whether"
" you need to work, run a company, stay connected, or relax, the software "
"shipped with Linux is often beautiful, blazing fast, easy to use, and always"
" under your control. Most concerns about Linux are now outdated or unfounded"
" and your system will remain secure well beyond the end of Windows 10 date "
"at no cost."
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:36
msgid "The End Of 10 campaign has identified 5 reasons to upgrade to Linux:"
msgstr ""

#: content/press/2025-05-28-press-release/index.md:57
msgid ""
"If you're a gamer, you might be wondering: Can I still play my games on "
"Linux? Yes, you can, and it has never been easier! Thousands of popular AAA "
"games now run seamlessly on Linux and, in many cases, performance is equal "
"to or even better than on Windows, especially on older hardware."
msgstr ""

